description: The Trump administration today asked a federal appeals court for an emergency stay of last week’s order from a federal judge to remove the National Guard from Washington, DC. #CNN #News
title: Trump admin files emergency motion to keep National Guard in DC after shooting

author: CNN
description: The two National Guardsmen who were shot today in downtown Washington, DC, are in critical condition, FBI Director Kash Patel and DC Mayor Muriel Bowser said during a news conference. “To the American public and the world, please send your prayers to those brave warriors who are in critical condition and their families,” Patel said. #CNN #News
title: Hear the DC officials' news conference clarifying today's shooting

author: CNN
description: Two members of the West Virginia National Guard were shot in Washington, DC, today, according to the state’s governor. They engaged in gunfire with the suspected shooter prior to being shot, according to two law enforcement sources. The sources said the suspect was detained and transported away from the scene on a stretcher. A source familiar with the investigation says that there are no other victims of Wednesday's shooting beyond the two National Guard officers and the suspect. #CNN #News
title: 2 National Guardsmen shot near White House, suspect in custody and 'severely wounded'

title: Post-Thanksgiving cross-country winter storm could wreck travel

author: CNN
description:
This year’s Thanksgiving travel period is expected to be the busiest in 15 years, according to the Federal Aviation Administration. About 73 million are projected to hit the road, with an estimated 6 million set to take to the skies. It’s getting cold for some parts of the country as a blast of Arctic air moves east. But traveling through airports has been pretty smooth so far, with only a few disruptions due to weather.

CNN aviation correspondent Pete Muntean reports from Reagan Washington National Airport, and Pamela Brown speaks with Eric Rosen, director of travel content at The Points Guy. #CNN #News
title: Millions packing roads, airports in holiday travel rush

author: CNN
description:
Two National Guardsmen were shot in Washington, DC, on Wednesday, according to Homeland Security Secretary Kristi Noem. The shooting occurred in downtown Washington, DC, on Wednesday, according to a source familiar with the early reports and a law enforcement official. DC Metropolitan Police said on X that the scene is secure and one suspect is in custody. They advised people to avoid the area. The National Guard did not immediately respond to request for comment. The circumstances of the shooting are not immediately clear.

Boris Sanchez and Omar Jimenez are joined by CNN senior law enforcement analyst and former FBI deputy director Andrew McCabe. #CNN #News
title: DHS: Two National Guardsmen shot near White House; police say suspect in custody

author: CNN
description:
A Georgia prosecutor on Wednesday officially dropped the historic racketeering case against President Donald Trump and others for attempting to overturn the 2020 presidential election, closing the chapter in a legal effort once seen as a grave threat to Trump’s political future. The move means that Trump has dodged criminal legal jeopardy for his attempts to overturn his 2020 election loss to President Joe Biden. The federal cases against Trump from special counsel Jack Smith on election interference leading up to the January 6, 2021, US Capitol riot and mishandling classified documents were previously dropped.

CNN correspondents Kara Scannell and Kristen Holmes report, and Pamela Brown speaks with CNN senior legal analyst and former assistant US attorney Elie Honig. #CNN #News
title: Georgia 2020 election fraud charges against Trump dropped

description:
The FBI is seeking to schedule interviews with the six Democratic lawmakers who, in a controversial video posted last week, urged service members and intelligence officials to disobey illegal orders. The six – Sens. Mark Kelly and Elissa Slotkin, and Reps. Chrissy Houlahan, Chris Deluzio, Jason Crow and Maggie Goodlander – were quickly attacked on Truth Social by President Donald Trump, who called them traitors and suggested they engaged in “SEDITIOUS BEHAVIOR, punishable by DEATH!”

Kaitlan Collins is joined on "The Source" by CNN senior law enforcement analyst and former FBI deputy director Andrew McCabe, CNN senior legal analyst and former US attorney Elie Honig and former Trump campaign manager Bill Stepien. #CNN #News
title: FBI & Pentagon launch investigations into Dem video

author: CNN
description: Started in 1988, as a way to celebrate the international cheese scene, the World Cheese Awards is one of the biggest events of the year for dairy producers, gathering record amounts of cheese in one giant aroma-filled venue. This year’s edition featured 5,244 cheeses from 46 countries but only one could be crowned the grand winner. CNN’s Barry Neild went behind the scenes of the awards in Bern, Switzerland to find out how the judges taste their way to a decision. #cnn #cnntravel
title: World’s Best Cheese 2025
